"title": "5652: babies",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5652",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The gift of young children from God is usually seen as a blessing. The term is also used figuratively of those who are young or immature in the faith.</p>\n<h2>Babies as a blessing from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:3\">PSA 127:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:28\">GEN 1:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:16\">GEN 17:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:59-Gen24:60\">GEN 24:59–24:60</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:6\">PRO 17:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:41-Luke1:42\">LUK 1:41–1:42</a></p>\n<h2>The promise of a baby</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:15-Gen17:19\">GEN 17:15–17:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:10-Gen18:14\">GEN 18:10–18:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:14-2Kgs4:17\">2KI 4:14–4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:11-Luke1:24\">LUK 1:11–1:24</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of biblical characters as babies</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:1-Gen21:7\">GEN 21:1–21:7</a> <em>Isaac</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:21-Gen25:26\">GEN 25:21–25:26</a> <em>Esau and Jacob</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:1-Exod2:10\">EXO 2:1–2:10</a> <em>Moses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:2-Judg13:25\">JDG 13:2–13:25</a> <em>Samson</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:13-Ruth4:17\">RUT 4:13–4:17</a> <em>Obed, the father of Jesse</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:24-2Sam12:25\">2SA 12:24–12:25</a> <em>Solomon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:57-Luke1:66\">LUK 1:57–1:66</a> <em>John the Baptist</em></p>\n<h2>Babies as prophetic signs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14\">ISA 7:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:3-Isa8:4\">ISA 8:3–8:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6-Isa9:7\">ISA 9:6–9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:2-Hos1:11\">HOS 1:2–1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:8-Luke2:12\">LUK 2:8–2:12</a></p>\n<h2>OT laws concerned with the birth of babies</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:21-Luke2:24\">LUK 2:21–2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:9-Gen17:12\">GEN 17:9–17:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:1-Exod13:2\">EXO 13:1–13:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:1-Lev12:8\">LEV 12:1–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:59\">LUK 1:59</a></p>\n<h2>A mother's love for her baby</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:15\">ISA 49:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:16-1Kgs3:28\">1KI 3:16–3:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:12-Isa66:13\">ISA 66:12–66:13</a></p>\n<h2>Babies are sinful from birth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:5\">PSA 51:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps58:3\">PSA 58:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:34\">JHN 9:34</a></p>\n<h2>The death of babies</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:15-Exod1:22\">EXO 1:15–1:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod11:4-Exod11:5\">EXO 11:4–11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:13-2Sam12:23\">2SA 12:13–12:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:11-Lam2:12\">LAM 2:11–2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:16-Matt2:18\">MAT 2:16–2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:17-Acts7:19\">ACT 7:17–7:19</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ and babies</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's own birth and babyhood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:18-Matt1:23\">MAT 1:18–1:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14\">ISA 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:1-Matt2:23\">MAT 2:1–2:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:26-Luke1:38\">LUK 1:26–1:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:1-Luke2:40\">LUK 2:1–2:40</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's response to babies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:15-Luke18:17\">LUK 18:15–18:17</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:13-Matt19:15\">MAT 19:13–19:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:13-Mark10:16\">MRK 10:13–10:16</a></p>\n<h2>Babyhood used as a spiritual image</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:1-1Cor3:2\">1CO 3:1–3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:2\">PSA 8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:16\">MAT 21:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:25\">MAT 11:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:20\">ROM 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:20\">1CO 14:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:14\">EPH 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:11-Heb5:14\">HEB 5:11–5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:2-1Pet2:3\">1PE 2:2–2:3</a></p>",
